@startuml 03_FileUploadFlow
participant User
participant "API Controller" as Controller
participant "FileService" as FileService
participant "Database" as DB
participant "Filesystem" as FS

User -> Controller: POST /tasks/{id}/attachments\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\nFile: document.pdf (5MB)
activate Controller

Controller -> Controller: validateToken()
Controller -> DB: verifyUserRole(userId)
DB --> Controller: role=Member

Controller -> DB: SELECT project_id FROM tasks\nWHERE id=?
DB --> Controller: project_id=123

Controller -> DB: SELECT * FROM project_members\nWHERE project_id=123 AND user_id=?\nAND deleted_at IS NULL
note right: Verify user is team member,\naccess to this project
DB --> Controller: member record exists

Controller -> FileService: uploadFile(file, taskId, userId)
activate FileService

FileService -> FileService: validateFileType(document.pdf)
note right: Check whitelist:\npdf, doc, xlsx, etc.

FileService -> FileService: validateFileSize(5MB)
note right: Max 25MB per file

FileService -> FileService: generateUUID() + timestamp
note right: Create unique filename:\nuuid_timestamp.pdf

FileService -> FS: write to\n/projects/123/tasks/{id}/\nattachments/{uuid}_{ts}.pdf
activate FS
FS --> FileService: success
deactivate FS

FileService -> DB: INSERT INTO attachments\n(task_id, uploaded_by, filename,\noriginal_name, size, mimetype, path,\ncreated_at)
DB --> FileService: attachment_id=456

FileService -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_logs\n(action='FILE_UPLOAD', user_id,\nresource_id, created_at)
DB --> FileService: audit recorded

FileService --> Controller: {attachmentId: 456, url}
deactivate FileService

Controller --> User: 200 OK\n{attachmentId, downloadUrl}
deactivate Controller

note over Controller, FS: File access controlled by DB check:\nonly project members can download

User -> Controller: GET /attachments/{attachmentId}
activate Controller
Controller -> DB: SELECT a.*, p.id as project_id\nFROM attachments a\nJOIN tasks t ON a.task_id=t.id\nJOIN projects p ON t.project_id=p.id\nWHERE a.id={attachmentId}
DB --> Controller: attachment + project_id

Controller -> DB: verifyUserInProject(userId, project_id)
note right: Check user is team member\nbefore allowing download
DB --> Controller: verified

Controller -> FS: read file from path
FS --> Controller: file stream
Controller --> User: 200 OK + file download
deactivate Controller

@enduml
